Business Brief -- TriMas Corp.:
   Firm Plans Public Offering
   Totaling 4 Million Shares
The company, based in Ann Arbor, Mich., said it filed a
registration statement for the offering with the Securities
and Exchange Commission on Monday. The offering will be
managed by Lehman Brothers, a division of the Shearson Lehman
Brothers unit of American Express, and PaineWebber Inc.
Currently, TriMas has 9.8 million shares of common stock
outstanding.
   Brian P. Campbell, TriMas president said the offering is,
"a question of strengthening our balance sheet." In composite
trading on the New York Stock Exchange yesterday, TriMas
stock closed at $23.625 a share, down 75 cents.